gallery/qsHxzAw</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Tzmca2C.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>One love.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/qsHxzAw</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Bruskey]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The last words of Thorin Oakenshield</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/BCUBOVK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/4hA7yVe.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is a look at the profound message by the king to the burglar in The Hobbit.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pSh5GwO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Thorin and Bilbo Baggins had parted on unfriendly terms at the gate of the Lonely Mountain, as Thorin was consumed by greed for its treasure hoard (art by Alan Lee).</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vWtTpG4.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Next day occurred the Battle of the Five Armies when two hosts of Orcs and Wargs attacked, forcing the Dwarves to ally with Men and Elves. The unexpected allies won the day but not before the Dwarf-king had fallen (art by Lucas Graciano).</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GrTuhQx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>After the battle Bilbo was brought into a tent by the Wizard Gandalf, to meet the old dwarf ere it was too late (The Hobbit; XVIII onwards, art by Darrell Sweet with edits):

“There indeed lay Thorin Oakenshield, wounded with many wounds, and his rent armour and notched axe were cast upon the floor.”</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/OeHrFec.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Thorin greeted the thief and told that he would pass on to the halls of his forefathers, thus leaving “all gold and silver, and go where it is of little worth”; and that he regretted his words and deeds at the gate (art by Jef Murray).</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lNHIStM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>“Bilbo knelt on one knee filled with sorrow. `Farewell, King under the Mountain!´ he said. `This is a bitter adventure, if it must end so; and not a mountain of gold can amend it. Yet I am glad that I have shared in your perils - that has been more than any Baggins deserves.´”</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hOQCxxR.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>“`Oh my god!´ said Thorin. `I am never gonna financially recover from this. Farewell!´”

